Implemented in `elisp.ts` and `index.ts`:

- `isPath` now requires a leading `/`, `./`, or `../` (not just any `/` anywhere)
- Buffer-name fallback when no existing buffer found:
  - Name contains special chars (`*`, `/`, `<`, `>`) → `get-buffer-create` (no file association)
  - Plain name → `find-file-noselect "./<name>"` (file-associated, as if preceded by `./`)
- Removed now-redundant `(is-path ...)` let* binding from generated elisp
- Updated `name` parameter descriptions in both `read` and `write` tools, mentioning `*name*` convention for temp buffers
- `write` already used `(when (buffer-file-name) (save-buffer))`, so save-only-if-file was already correct
- Added 18 new unit tests covering all classification cases
- Updated stale test "save default does not save" → "save default saves when buffer has file"

All 374 tests pass.
